newsArray.title: Georgia oligarch to award national football team $10 million
creator: rbksa
newsArray.description: Author: AFPID: 1719497109353320900Thu, 2024-06-27 17:12TBILISI: Georgia’s powerful oligarch Bidzina Ivanishvili will award the country’s national football team $10 million after they made it to the last 16 of Euro 2024, his ruling party said Thursday.Georgia’s 2-0 win over Portugal on Wednesday was a historic triumph in the Black Sea nation’s first appearance at a major international tournament.Coached by Frenchman Willy Sagnol, the team qualified from Group F as one of the four best third-placed finishers and face a daunting clash with Spain, who won all their group games, on Sunday.Main category: FootballSportTags: Euro 2024GeorgiaPortugalWilly Sagnol
